  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut half of your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to one side of the baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 30-35 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2536Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2536Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2536Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2536Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2536Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and grate the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>potato[es]</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>grated potato</strong> to the middle of a tea towel and bring the four corners together to form a ball</p><p>Twist the ball and squeeze out as much of the liquid as you can</p><p>Add the <strong>squeezed potato</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>smoked paprika</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>paprika potato mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2536Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2536Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2536Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2536Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2536Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into rounds (approx. 1cm thick)</p><p>Once the chips have had an initial 15 minutes, remove the tray from the oven and add the <strong>red onion rounds</strong> to the other side</p><p>Drizzle <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) over the red onion rounds with a little <strong>olive oil</strong> and return to the oven until caramelised and crispy – these are your <strong>balsamic onions</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2536Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2536Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2536Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2536Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2536Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>paprika potato mixture</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until crispy and golden – these are your<strong> speedy paprika röstis</strong></p><p>Tip: Don't worry how they look, you're just after the crunch!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2536Step-4-x200.jpg",
